NAME:	queue-submission-test-sh

DESCRIPTION:	This is the main script that runs all the other scripts to test BES job submission, stage-in and  stage-out 

INPUT:	inputfile.txt
	Contents of inputfile.txt
	GENII_INSTALL_DIR : GenesisII client is installation path
	DEPLOYMENT_NAME	: deployment name you want to use (usually default)
	GENII_USER_DIR : GenesisII state directory path (usually ~/.genesisII-2.0)
	QUEUE_PATH  : Path tp Grid queue on which jobs will be submitted
	RNSPATH  : Grid path where you can stage-in and stage out the files. 

OUTPUT:		env-file, Job Tickets for all the jobs submitted

USAGE/EXAMPLE:		./queue-submission-test-sh
	
LIMITATIONS:	Should have properly set all the environment variables in inputfile.txt

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

NAME:	ls-single-job.jsdl
	
DESCRIPTION:	Submits a single 'ls' job to specified queue

INPUT:	N/A

OUTPUT: Ticket Number for the job

USAGE/EXAMPLE: <GenesisII-Install-Dir>/grid qsub <grid-queue-path> local:<local-path>/ls-single-job.jsdl

LIMITATIONS: None

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

NAME:   hostname-sleep-60s.jsdl

DESCRIPTION:    Submits a single 'hostname' job to specified queue,
job sleeps for 60s

INPUT:  N/A

OUTPUT: Ticket Number for the job

USAGE/EXAMPLE: <GenesisII-Install-Dir>/grid qsub <grid-queue-path>
local:<local-path>/hostname-sleep-60s.jsdl

LIMITATIONS:    None

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

NAME:   hostname-stage-out.jsdl

DESCRIPTION:    Submits a single 'hostname' job to specified queue,
stages-out the output.txt to user's grid home directory

INPUT:  N/A

OUTPUT: Ticket Number for the job, output.txt

USAGE/EXAMPLE: <GenesisII-Install-Dir>/grid qsub <grid-queue-path>
local:<local-path>/hostname-stage-out.jsdl

LIMITATIONS: None

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

NAME:   cat-stdin-stageout.jsdl

DESCRIPTION:    Submits a 'cat' job that takes filename as input and
cat's the filename to a output file.

INPUT:  File name to be 'cat'

OUTPUT: File that has 'cat' output (cat.out, cat.err)

USAGE/EXAMPLE:  <GenesisII-Install-Dir>/grid qsub <grid-queue-path>
local:<local-path>/cat-stdin-stageout.jsdl

LIMITATIONS: Input file name should exist

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

NAME:   hostname-sweep-100.jsdl

DESCRIPTION:    Submits 100 'hostname' jobs to specified queue,
staging in the executable

INPUT: N/A

OUTPUT: 100 Ticket Numbers for the job

USAGE/EXAMPLE: <GenesisII-Install-Dir>/grid qsub <grid-queue-path>
local:<local-path>/hostname-stageout-parameter-sweep-100.jsdl

LIMITATIONS: None

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

NAME: 	ls-parameter-sweep-1000.jsdl

DESCRIPTION:	Submits 1000 'ls' job to specified queue (parameter sweep)

INPUT: N/A

OUTPUT:	1000 Ticket Number for the job

USAGE/EXAMPLE: <GenesisII-Install-Dir>/grid qsub <grid-queue-path> local:<local-path>/ls-parameter-sweep-1000.jsdl

LIMITATIONS: None

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

NAME:	ls-submit-1000.xml

DESCRIPTION: Xscript that submits 1000 'ls' jobs (one job at a time, not parameter sweep)

INPUT: Path to the grid queue

OUTPUT: 100 job ticket numbers 

USAGE/EXAMPLE:	<GenesisII-Install-Dir>/grid script local:./ls-submit-1000.xml $QUEUE_PATH	

LIMITATIONS:	None 
